<title>Learning Curve</title>


</head>
<body background=3D"https://shemesh.larc.nasa.gov/images/fm-background.jpg"=
>
<h1 align=3D"center">Learning Curve</h1>

Many people use the phrase "steep learning curve" to refer to something tha=
t
is difficult to learn.
This makes sense if one thinks of plotting <i>amount to be learned</i>
vs. <i>time</i>.
If one plots <i>amount learned</i> vs. <i>time</i>, then
a steep (or short) learning curve is a good thing, because it indicates
that a large amount of learning is taking place in a short period of time.
In contrast, a shallow (or long) learning curve indicates that a
long period of time is required to learn the needed information.


</body></html>
